IN	4 cups seedless red grapes
IN	3/4 cup Champagne or sparkling wine
IN	1/2 cup sugar
IN	1/4 cup frozen Concord grape juice concentrate, thawed
IN	Few pinches of ground cinnamon
IN	Additional seedless red grapes (for garnish; optional)
PR	Puree 4 cups grapes in blender. Combine Champagne, sugar, juice concentrate, 1/4 cup water, and cinnamon in bowl; add 11/2 cups grape puree (reserve any remaining puree for another use). Stir until sugar dissolves.
PR	Process mixture in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's instructions. Transfer to container. Cover and freeze until firm, at least 4 hours and up to 2 days.
PR	Serve sorbet in Champagne coupes: garnish with additional grapes, if desired.
